- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and their properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses efficient algorithms for checking the regularity of languages. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper may involve analyzing the complexity of the algorithms used. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with counting subwords, which is a combinatorial problem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve information-theoretic concepts in analyzing the regularity of languages.
